Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          William Shakespeare
Lived:         1564 - 1616
Nationality:   English
Field:         Literature
Known For:     Hamlet, Romeo and Juliet
Contribution:  38 plays; 154 sonnets; invented 1,700+ English words
Quote:         "All the world's a stage."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

