============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is relativity?
A1: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q2: What is natural selection?
A2: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

Q3: What is the Big Bang?
A3: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q4: What is gravity?
A4: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q5: What is machine learning?
A5: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

